WEBVTT

00:03.046 --> 00:04.700
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.787 --> 00:06.441
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.528 --> 00:08.573
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.660 --> 00:10.314
♪ Hey ♪

00:10.401 --> 00:12.099
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.186 --> 00:13.839
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.926 --> 00:16.146
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.233 --> 00:19.323
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day ♪

00:19.410 --> 00:21.543
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.630 --> 00:23.414
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.501 --> 00:28.158
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.245 --> 00:31.161
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.248 --> 00:33.511
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day ♪

00:33.598 --> 00:34.599
- Whoo-hoo!

00:36.036 --> 00:38.821
[upbeat music]

00:38.908 --> 00:45.828
♪ ♪

00:45.915 --> 00:47.786
- Hi, Peter.

00:47.873 --> 00:50.267
We're here to pick up our
flowers for the salon.

00:50.354 --> 00:52.835
- Hi, everyone.
Be right with you.

00:52.922 --> 00:54.489
- A talking plant.

00:54.576 --> 00:56.404
We should get one of those
for the salon.

00:56.491 --> 00:59.668
- Or one of these.

00:59.755 --> 01:01.365
It's beautiful.

01:01.452 --> 01:04.020
- Wow, it is beautiful.
- Ah.

01:04.107 --> 01:06.153
- Can we get one of those
for the salon?

01:06.240 --> 01:08.285
Ooh, can we, Sunny?Can we?

01:08.372 --> 01:09.373
[door closing]
- Ah, ah, ah.

01:09.460 --> 01:11.201
I'm afraid you can't
have that one.

01:11.288 --> 01:13.812
That's my prize-winning
three-headed rose.

01:13.899 --> 01:16.032
It's very special.

01:16.119 --> 01:17.512
- Wow.
- Pretty.

01:17.599 --> 01:18.991
- [sniffs]
Ah.

01:19.079 --> 01:21.081
Peter, it smells so sweet.

01:21.168 --> 01:23.431
- [sniffs]
It's very rare.

01:23.518 --> 01:25.346
I've been growing it for years.

01:25.433 --> 01:28.827
And now it's won Best Flower
in "Flower Monthly Magazine."

01:28.914 --> 01:31.134
We're going to be on the cover
of the next issue.

01:31.221 --> 01:33.658
The photographer's coming later
to take our picture.

01:33.745 --> 01:36.618
- Go, Peter.
And go, Peter's rose.

01:36.705 --> 01:38.098
- [laughs]
Thanks.

01:38.185 --> 01:40.752
This little rose and I
are really close.

01:40.839 --> 01:42.450
[upbeat music]

01:42.537 --> 01:44.713
♪ Oh, my rose ♪

01:44.800 --> 01:46.889
♪ You're so beautiful to me ♪

01:46.976 --> 01:49.283
♪ And though you're
in good company ♪

01:49.370 --> 01:51.589
♪ You're one of a kind ♪

01:51.676 --> 01:53.765
♪ What about those ♪

01:53.852 --> 01:56.028
♪ Who say your beauty's
not for them ♪

01:56.116 --> 01:58.161
♪ You've got three blossoms
on one stem ♪

01:58.248 --> 02:00.381
♪ But that's just fine ♪

02:00.468 --> 02:02.426
♪ I see the colors
all around you ♪

02:02.513 --> 02:04.080
♪ But to me,
you really shine ♪

02:04.167 --> 02:05.473
♪ There's something
about lilies ♪

02:05.560 --> 02:07.388
♪ Something about daisies ♪

02:07.475 --> 02:09.694
♪ Something about poppies
drives my heart crazy ♪

02:09.781 --> 02:11.914
♪ I love every kind
of flower ♪

02:12.001 --> 02:14.264
♪ And it shows ♪

02:14.351 --> 02:16.310
♪ But there's only
one for me ♪

02:16.397 --> 02:19.051
♪ She's beauty times three ♪

02:19.139 --> 02:22.359
♪ Oh, my rose ♪

02:22.446 --> 02:24.927
♪ My three-headed rose ♪

02:25.014 --> 02:26.450
♪ Oh, there's something
about tulips ♪

02:26.537 --> 02:28.104
♪ Something about clover ♪

02:28.191 --> 02:30.150
♪ Makes me smile
over and over ♪

02:30.237 --> 02:34.763
♪ I love every kind of flower
and it shows ♪

02:34.850 --> 02:36.721
♪ But there's only
one for me ♪

02:36.808 --> 02:39.202
♪ She's beauty times three ♪

02:39.289 --> 02:42.814
♪ Oh, my rose ♪

02:42.901 --> 02:47.297
♪ My three-headed rose ♪

02:47.384 --> 02:49.038
Ah.

02:49.125 --> 02:51.301
I wish I could stay
and look after it,

02:51.388 --> 02:54.522
but I promised to arrange
the flowers at the palace.

02:54.609 --> 02:56.088
Don't worry, rose.

02:56.176 --> 02:59.657
You won't be too lonely
without me, right?

02:59.744 --> 03:02.312
- Well, why don't we look
after it for the day?

03:02.399 --> 03:04.140
- Really?
You wouldn't mind?

03:04.227 --> 03:05.968
- Happy to help.

03:06.055 --> 03:07.970
- We'll take really good care
of it till you're back.

03:08.057 --> 03:09.928
- That'd be great.

03:10.015 --> 03:13.715
All you need to do is give it
exactly three drops of water.

03:13.802 --> 03:16.196
- Three drops of water.
Got it.

03:16.283 --> 03:18.023
- Yep.
Don't worry.

03:18.110 --> 03:20.374
We're all over this.
- Uh-huh.

03:20.461 --> 03:21.984
- Thanks, everyone.

03:22.071 --> 03:24.682
Hey, don't forget your flowers
for the salon.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.293
- [shouting]

03:26.380 --> 03:30.601
- Oh, and here's a few extra
to say thanks.

03:30.688 --> 03:31.646
both: Oh.
- Buh-bye.

03:31.733 --> 03:32.951
- [groans]

03:33.038 --> 03:35.258
all: [grunting]

03:35.345 --> 03:36.825
- Don't worry, little rose.

03:36.912 --> 03:39.001
We'll take good care
of you for Peter.

03:39.088 --> 03:41.308
- We won't let anything
happen to you.

03:41.395 --> 03:42.309
Right, Blair?

03:42.396 --> 03:43.571
[grunts]
Blair!

03:43.658 --> 03:45.181
- Whoa!
- Oh!

03:45.268 --> 03:48.097
Oh, no!
Oh!

03:48.184 --> 03:49.968
Whew.

03:50.055 --> 03:52.275
- Phew.
Good save, Sunny.

03:52.362 --> 03:55.235
At least the rose will
be safe in the salon.

03:55.322 --> 03:56.801
- Yep, safe and sound.

03:56.888 --> 04:00.805
♪ ♪

04:00.892 --> 04:02.981
- [barks]

04:03.068 --> 04:04.461
- [giggles]

04:04.548 --> 04:06.376
- Whoa!
[both laughing]

04:06.463 --> 04:08.378
A little here.

04:08.465 --> 04:11.033
- Oh, Doodle, play.
- [barks]

04:11.120 --> 04:12.382
Play, play!

04:12.469 --> 04:14.123
- Sorry, Violet.
Sorry, Rosie.

04:14.210 --> 04:16.517
Can't play today.
Very important job.

04:16.604 --> 04:19.128
I'm on three-headed rose
guarding duty.

04:19.215 --> 04:20.825
both: Oh.

04:20.912 --> 04:23.393
- We help.
- I dunno.

04:23.480 --> 04:26.309
It's a lot of responsibility.

04:26.396 --> 04:28.920
both: Huh.
- We responsible.

04:30.487 --> 04:32.663
Halt.
- No go there.

04:32.750 --> 04:35.231
- Wow, you really do
look responsible.

04:35.318 --> 04:37.320
Let's get some snacks
before we continue.

04:37.407 --> 04:39.061
both: [gasp]
- Guarding is hungry work.

04:39.148 --> 04:40.497
To the pet parlor!

04:40.584 --> 04:42.238
- [barking]

04:42.325 --> 04:44.936
- A quick blow dry and
you'll be done in no time.

04:45.023 --> 04:46.068
[dryer blowing]

04:46.155 --> 04:48.853
- Magazines, check.

04:48.940 --> 04:52.204
Shampoo, check.
Hmm.

04:52.292 --> 04:55.295
Laundry cleanup, check.
Hmm.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.427
Water three-headed rose.

04:57.514 --> 05:00.169
[twinkling]

05:00.256 --> 05:02.824
One, two, three drops.

05:02.911 --> 05:04.304
Ah.

05:04.391 --> 05:07.089
Watered three-headed rose,
check.

05:07.176 --> 05:10.005
What's next?
Ah, hair gel.

05:11.572 --> 05:13.791
- Lacey and KC
are gonna love these--

05:13.878 --> 05:16.925
perfect purple pet chalks
for the pet parlor.

05:17.012 --> 05:20.189
Speaking of perfect,
how's our rose?

05:20.276 --> 05:22.974
Hmm, you look thirsty.

05:23.061 --> 05:25.499
I'll just give you
a little drink.

05:25.586 --> 05:28.197
One, two, three drops.

05:28.284 --> 05:29.981
You're welcome.

05:30.068 --> 05:33.594
[rumbling]

05:33.681 --> 05:35.465
- There you go.
- Thanks, Sunny.

05:35.552 --> 05:37.685
See you soon.
- Bye, June.

05:37.772 --> 05:40.340
Have a sunny day.
[door bell jingles]

05:40.427 --> 05:42.646
Hey, how are you doing?

05:42.733 --> 05:45.649
Has anyone watered
Peter's rose yet?

05:45.736 --> 05:47.477
Rox?
Blair?

05:47.564 --> 05:48.913
Doodle?

05:49.000 --> 05:50.393
Hmm.

05:50.480 --> 05:53.135
One, two, three drops.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.398
There you go.
[door bell jingles]

05:55.485 --> 05:57.182
Hi, Eric.
- Hey, Sunny.

05:57.269 --> 05:58.358
- You're right on time.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.620
Come this way.

05:59.707 --> 06:02.057
[suspenseful music]

06:02.144 --> 06:03.711
[rumbling]

06:03.798 --> 06:07.062
♪ ♪

06:07.149 --> 06:08.193
[door opens]

06:08.280 --> 06:10.805
- Oh.

06:10.892 --> 06:12.459
- Did Sunny call me?

06:12.546 --> 06:15.549
Something about
watering the rose?

06:15.636 --> 06:16.637
- I dunno.
- [squeaks]

06:16.724 --> 06:19.553
- Don't worry, Sunny.
I'm on it.

06:19.640 --> 06:22.164
Hey, I bet
you need a snack, too.

06:24.645 --> 06:27.778
[dramatic music]

06:27.865 --> 06:29.693
Okay, back to guarding.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.479
♪ ♪

06:32.566 --> 06:34.829
- Thanks for the trim, Sunny.
- You're welcome.

06:34.916 --> 06:36.134
Come back soon.
[door bell jingles]

06:36.221 --> 06:39.137
- That's our last customer.Check.

06:39.224 --> 06:40.530
Let's see.

06:40.617 --> 06:43.098
I've replaced the towels,
sorted the shampoos,

06:43.185 --> 06:46.014
and watered Peter's rose.

06:46.101 --> 06:47.581
- But I watered Peter's rose.

06:47.668 --> 06:49.278
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

06:49.365 --> 06:51.541
- Wait, you both watered it?

06:51.628 --> 06:53.238
But I watered it, too.

06:53.325 --> 06:55.415
- [gasps]

06:55.502 --> 06:57.852
- Um, Rox, Peter's rose...

06:57.939 --> 07:01.072
- Yep, don't worry.
I totally watered it.

07:01.159 --> 07:03.248
- That means we all watered it.

07:03.335 --> 07:06.295
But Peter said we should
only give it three drops.

07:06.382 --> 07:08.819
- At least it won't be thirsty
for a while.

07:08.906 --> 07:12.475
I mean, what's the worst
that can happen?

07:12.562 --> 07:14.216
all: [gasping]

07:14.303 --> 07:17.175
[screaming]

07:17.262 --> 07:20.135
- Um, maybe Peter won't notice?

07:20.222 --> 07:22.354
all: He'll notice.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.487
- And the photographer's coming
today to take its picture

07:24.574 --> 07:26.576
for the magazine cover.

07:26.663 --> 07:27.969
- Nobody panic.

07:28.056 --> 07:30.580
Maybe we could revive it.

07:30.667 --> 07:33.931
- So, to recap,
the rosesitting for Peter

07:34.018 --> 07:37.413
isn't going so great
and now you plan to save it

07:37.500 --> 07:39.415
with a...
- Doggie biscuit.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.461
Yep.
- Never gonna work.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.201
♪ ♪

07:43.288 --> 07:47.292
- It was a nice idea, Doodle,
but I think dog biscuits

07:47.379 --> 07:48.293
only work on dogs.

07:48.380 --> 07:49.860
- Good try, Doodle.

07:49.947 --> 07:51.471
- Any other ideas?

07:51.558 --> 07:53.385
- Okay, here's
what I'm thinking.

07:53.473 --> 07:56.388
I bet we've got everything
we need to perk up this rose

07:56.476 --> 07:58.521
right here in the pet parlor.

07:58.608 --> 07:59.740
[machine beeping]

07:59.827 --> 08:01.263
[whirring]

08:01.350 --> 08:04.222
[dryers blowing]

08:04.309 --> 08:06.442
♪ ♪

08:06.529 --> 08:08.836
That did not work.

08:08.923 --> 08:11.534
But, hey, the rose is warmer.

08:11.621 --> 08:13.318
- Why don't we try shampoo?

08:13.405 --> 08:15.625
This makes Doodle's
hair feel great.

08:15.712 --> 08:17.192
- It sure does.

08:17.279 --> 08:20.195
- Maybe it'll make the flower
feel great, too.

08:20.282 --> 08:22.502
[bubbles popping]

08:24.895 --> 08:27.550
- Well, at least it still
has one petal left.

08:27.637 --> 08:30.205
[bubbles popping]

08:30.292 --> 08:31.467
- Not anymore.

08:31.554 --> 08:34.426
- We've really let him down.

08:34.514 --> 08:38.518
- And no three-headed rose
means no magazine cover.

08:38.605 --> 08:40.650
- Is it time to panic?

08:40.737 --> 08:42.173
all: Yes.

08:45.960 --> 08:48.876
- We had one job--
to look after the rose,

08:48.963 --> 08:50.442
and we failed.

08:50.530 --> 08:53.663
- Wait, what if we find
another three-headed rose?

08:53.750 --> 08:56.231
That way Peter could still
be on the magazine cover.

08:56.318 --> 08:58.929
- But Peter said
the flower's really rare.

08:59.016 --> 09:00.844
We'll never find one in time.

09:00.931 --> 09:02.454
- Never say never, Blair.

09:02.542 --> 09:05.066
There are lots of roses
in Friendly Falls Woods.

09:05.153 --> 09:07.459
One of them must
have three heads.

09:07.547 --> 09:10.462
Rosie, Violet, you stay
and look after the salon

09:10.550 --> 09:11.594
with Lacey and KC.

09:11.681 --> 09:13.117
both: You got it.

09:13.204 --> 09:15.380
- We're going three-headed
rose hunting.

09:15.467 --> 09:19.297
- Good luck.
- You'll need it.

09:19.384 --> 09:20.777
- Okay, team.

09:20.864 --> 09:22.779
Ready, set...

09:22.866 --> 09:24.999
all: Gear up and go!

09:25.086 --> 09:28.263
[bright music]

09:28.350 --> 09:32.093
♪ ♪

09:32.180 --> 09:34.312
[engine revving]

09:34.399 --> 09:40.492
♪ ♪

09:40.580 --> 09:43.757
- Now, let's find
a three-headed rose for Peter.

09:43.844 --> 09:46.368
- Hmm, where do we start?

09:46.455 --> 09:47.848
- I'm not sure.

09:47.935 --> 09:49.719
We'll just have
to look everywhere.

09:49.806 --> 09:51.373
Remember, this is for Peter.

09:51.460 --> 09:52.722
We can do this.

09:52.809 --> 09:55.290
- We'll find a three-headed
rose in no time.

09:55.377 --> 09:57.509
I'm an excellent sniffer dog.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.337
all: [laughing]

09:59.424 --> 10:01.165
- [sniffing]

10:04.386 --> 10:06.997
- No roses in the trees.

10:07.084 --> 10:09.870
- Bushes.
Maybe they'll have some roses.

10:09.957 --> 10:13.351
♪ ♪

10:13.438 --> 10:15.049
No roses.

10:15.136 --> 10:16.398
- Any luck, Doodle?

10:16.485 --> 10:18.835
- Definitely no roses here.

10:18.922 --> 10:20.097
A little help?

10:20.184 --> 10:22.012
all: [laughing]
- [grunts]

10:22.099 --> 10:23.492
- Thanks.

10:23.579 --> 10:26.582
- Come on.
Let's keep looking.

10:26.669 --> 10:28.889
- [sniffing]

10:28.976 --> 10:30.630
- Doodle,
do you smell something?

10:30.717 --> 10:33.371
- [sniffs]
This way!

10:33.458 --> 10:35.678
[sniffing]

10:35.765 --> 10:36.984
Ooh!
- Whoa!

10:37.071 --> 10:38.638
My raspberries!

10:38.725 --> 10:41.641
- [grunting]
[sighs]

10:41.728 --> 10:43.033
- You missed one.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.818
- Don't worry.
I got it.

10:44.905 --> 10:48.038
[chomps]
Mmm!

10:48.125 --> 10:49.953
- Sorry about that, Cindy.

10:50.040 --> 10:51.563
- That's okay.

10:51.651 --> 10:54.262
I've got plenty of berries
for my raspberry pancakes.

10:54.349 --> 10:56.743
- Did you say
raspberry pancakes?

10:56.830 --> 10:58.875
Yum!
- Yep.

10:58.962 --> 11:00.790
I'm making them
later at the bakery.

11:00.877 --> 11:04.141
- You didn't happen to see
a three-headed rose, did you?

11:04.228 --> 11:05.882
- Hmm.

11:05.969 --> 11:08.493
I think I saw some roses
earlier in the maple grove.

11:08.580 --> 11:10.539
- Great.
Thanks, Cindy.

11:10.626 --> 11:11.975
- Save me a pancake.

11:12.062 --> 11:13.629
- Back to the Glam Van,
everyone.

11:13.716 --> 11:15.065
- Bye.

11:15.152 --> 11:20.418
♪ ♪

11:20.505 --> 11:23.465
- Let's check those bushes
over there.

11:23.552 --> 11:25.162
[squishing]

11:25.249 --> 11:27.774
- Uh, why am I not moving?
[both grunting]

11:27.861 --> 11:29.645
- I'm stuck!
- Me, too.

11:29.732 --> 11:32.430
- [grunts]
Me, three.

11:32.517 --> 11:36.391
- Oh, I think
you're stuck in...syrup?

11:36.478 --> 11:38.785
- Did someone say syrup?

11:38.872 --> 11:40.569
girls: Timmy?
- Timmy?

11:40.656 --> 11:42.005
What are you doing here?

11:42.092 --> 11:43.964
- I was harvesting sap
from these maple trees

11:44.051 --> 11:45.705
to make maple syrup--

11:45.792 --> 11:48.490
oh, I make maple syrup,
you know--

11:48.577 --> 11:50.448
when I knocked over
this barrel,

11:50.535 --> 11:51.754
and I've been stuck ever since.

11:51.841 --> 11:53.277
- Don't worry, Timmy.

11:53.364 --> 11:55.932
I can get you all
out of this sticky situation.

11:56.019 --> 11:57.586
Let me see.

11:57.673 --> 11:59.196
- Mmm.
[licking]

11:59.283 --> 12:01.068
Still, maple syrup--

12:01.155 --> 12:04.288
if you're gonna be stuck,
this is as tasty as it gets.

12:04.375 --> 12:07.074
- Perfect--
my super sudsy shampoo.

12:07.161 --> 12:09.511
That should get you unstuck.

12:09.598 --> 12:11.600
- Yay, it's working!

12:11.687 --> 12:12.819
[shampoo sloshing]

12:12.906 --> 12:14.951
- We're free!

12:16.823 --> 12:20.130
all: [cheering]

12:20.217 --> 12:22.176
- Looks like that's it
for the shampoo.

12:22.263 --> 12:24.091
At least we got your feet free.

12:24.178 --> 12:26.223
- But we're still
surrounded by syrup.

12:26.310 --> 12:28.791
- If we step in it,
we'll get stuck again.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.837
[dramatic music]

12:30.924 --> 12:32.882
- No problem.

12:32.969 --> 12:37.321
Some ribbon,
a little braiding--here.

12:37.408 --> 12:39.889
[grunts]

12:39.976 --> 12:42.326
Hang on tight and swing across.

12:42.413 --> 12:45.329
both: Whoa!

12:45.416 --> 12:46.330
- Whoa!

12:46.417 --> 12:48.506
We did it!
Way to go, Sunny!

12:48.593 --> 12:50.770
♪ ♪

12:50.857 --> 12:52.641
both: Whoa!

12:52.728 --> 12:54.469
- We made it!
- Yippie!

12:54.556 --> 12:58.299
- Let me give you some syrup to
say thank you for rescuing me.

12:58.386 --> 13:00.954
- I think we've had enough
syrup for one day,

13:01.041 --> 13:02.782
but maybe you can help.

13:02.869 --> 13:06.307
Cindy said there might be
some roses growing here.

13:06.394 --> 13:09.092
We're after a very special
three-headed rose.

13:09.179 --> 13:11.138
- Three heads, you say?

13:11.225 --> 13:13.053
I think I've seen one
in my orchard.

13:13.140 --> 13:15.882
If you can find it,
it's all yours.

13:15.969 --> 13:17.535
all: [cheering]

13:17.622 --> 13:19.102
- Let's go.
We have to hurry.

13:19.189 --> 13:20.408
Peter will be back soon.

13:20.495 --> 13:22.758
[together]
Bye, Timmy.

13:22.845 --> 13:24.716
- Good luck.
Bye.

13:24.804 --> 13:26.544
Time to get back
to my maple syrup.

13:26.631 --> 13:28.720
Oh.
Hey.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.157
Stuck again?

13:30.244 --> 13:31.854
Oh.

13:34.291 --> 13:36.816
♪ ♪

13:36.903 --> 13:39.862
- Let's hope Timmy was right
about that three-headed rose.

13:42.343 --> 13:44.649
- This time we're definitely
gonna find our rose.

13:44.736 --> 13:46.173
Nothing can stop us.

13:46.260 --> 13:49.393
- Not sticky syrup--
- Or flying raspberries.

13:49.480 --> 13:52.614
- Uh, Sunny?
We may have a problem.

13:52.701 --> 13:56.270
[horse neighing]

13:56.357 --> 13:58.359
- That is something
you don't see every day.

13:58.446 --> 14:00.796
[horse whinnying]
- [sighs]

14:00.883 --> 14:04.713
Suzette, come back here!

14:04.800 --> 14:06.976
Oh, hi, everybody.

14:07.063 --> 14:09.196
- What's going on, Johnny-Ray?

14:09.283 --> 14:10.327
- We were playing
in the orchard,

14:10.414 --> 14:12.155
but Suzette's
having so much fun.

14:12.242 --> 14:14.244
She doesn't wanna stop.

14:14.331 --> 14:15.985
- [whinnying]
- [giggles]

14:16.072 --> 14:18.248
I think Suzette
wants us to play.

14:18.335 --> 14:19.771
- I know a good game
we can play.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.730
It's called, "Stop That Pony

14:21.817 --> 14:25.081
Before She Tramples
On Those Roses."

14:25.168 --> 14:27.736
- Quick!
She's heading right for them!

14:27.823 --> 14:29.781
- [whinnying]

14:29.869 --> 14:34.090
♪ ♪

14:34.177 --> 14:36.397
- Hey, whoa!
- [whinnying]

14:36.484 --> 14:37.528
- Hey!

14:37.615 --> 14:38.965
all: [panting]

14:39.052 --> 14:40.662
- [whinnying]
- Whoa!

14:40.749 --> 14:43.056
♪ ♪

14:43.143 --> 14:45.014
- [whinnying]
- [grunts]

14:46.407 --> 14:49.410
- Look out, Sunny!
- Whoa!

14:49.497 --> 14:52.674
Whoaaa!

14:52.761 --> 14:54.371
- Not the roses!

14:54.458 --> 14:57.070
- Whoa!

14:57.157 --> 14:59.463
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

14:59.550 --> 15:02.379
- Are you all right, Doodle?
- Everything's fine.

15:02.466 --> 15:04.642
I speak pony, remember?

15:04.729 --> 15:06.993
I'll just ask Suzette to stop.

15:07.080 --> 15:09.821
[whinnying]

15:09.909 --> 15:11.867
- [whinnying]

15:11.954 --> 15:14.609
- Whoa!

15:14.696 --> 15:16.524
- Grab hold.

15:16.611 --> 15:17.699
- We got you.

15:17.786 --> 15:20.180
♪ ♪

15:20.267 --> 15:22.791
Nice landing.

15:22.878 --> 15:24.227
- [grunts, whinnies]

15:24.314 --> 15:26.316
- Sunny!
The roses!

15:26.403 --> 15:29.145
- [grunts]
- [whinnying]

15:30.668 --> 15:32.757
[sniffs, whinnies]

15:32.844 --> 15:35.195
- I think that's enough
excitement for one day.

15:35.282 --> 15:36.892
Come on, Suzette.

15:36.979 --> 15:38.938
- [whinnies]

15:39.025 --> 15:42.463
- Quick, let's check
for three-headed roses.

15:42.550 --> 15:44.421
- There sure are a lot.

15:44.508 --> 15:47.120
But I don't see any
three-headed roses.

15:47.207 --> 15:49.426
- Let's check another
rose bush.

15:49.513 --> 15:51.602
- Hey, over there.

15:51.689 --> 15:53.909
[bright music]

15:53.996 --> 15:56.825
Could it be?

15:56.912 --> 15:58.522
It is!
Over here!

15:58.609 --> 16:00.785
I found one!

16:00.872 --> 16:03.092
- [laughs]
Yay!

16:03.179 --> 16:04.311
- Whoo-hoo!
- [barking]

16:04.398 --> 16:07.096
- Peter will have his
magazine cover after all.

16:07.183 --> 16:09.011
- [chomps]
- [gasps]

16:09.098 --> 16:10.795
[together] No!
- [gulps]

16:10.882 --> 16:13.407
[whinnies]

16:13.494 --> 16:15.235
- Sorry, Sunny.

16:15.322 --> 16:16.714
- That's it.

16:16.801 --> 16:19.848
we're officially out
of three-headed roses.

16:19.935 --> 16:23.547
- And we're out of time.
Peter will be back any minute.

16:26.072 --> 16:28.683
[tense music]

16:28.770 --> 16:30.902
- Time to tell Peter
what happened.

16:30.990 --> 16:33.514
- I hope he's not too upset.

16:34.819 --> 16:37.561
- Peter?

16:37.648 --> 16:40.086
- Hi, everyone.
You're just in time.

16:40.173 --> 16:41.652
The photographer
will be here soon.

16:41.739 --> 16:45.482
Imagine, me on the cover
of "Flower Monthly!"

16:45.569 --> 16:47.441
Now, where's my special
three-headed rose?

16:47.528 --> 16:49.443
- Yeah, about that.

16:49.530 --> 16:51.575
- You see, the thing is--
- We all watered it.

16:51.662 --> 16:53.360
- And it went like, "Eh."

16:53.447 --> 16:54.839
- So we tried
to revive it, but...

16:54.926 --> 16:57.451
- But roses do not
like blow-dryers.

16:57.538 --> 17:00.062
- Or shampoo.
- Or doggy biscuits.

17:00.149 --> 17:02.238
I know, hard to believe.

17:02.325 --> 17:03.718
- Blow-dryers?
Shampoo?

17:03.805 --> 17:05.502
Doggie biscuits?

17:05.589 --> 17:08.897
That sounds exhausting
and a little confusing.

17:08.984 --> 17:11.334
- So then we decided
to find a new rose, but--

17:11.421 --> 17:13.467
- There were so
many raspberries.

17:13.554 --> 17:16.252
And so much syrup.
- And so much Suzette.

17:16.339 --> 17:18.950
- You do have my flower, right?

17:19.038 --> 17:20.996
- We're so sorry, Peter,

17:21.083 --> 17:23.172
but we ruined your rose.

17:23.259 --> 17:24.826
- Hmm.

17:24.913 --> 17:27.220
Mm-hmm.

17:28.743 --> 17:30.788
[laughs]

17:30.875 --> 17:32.355
- What's so funny?

17:32.442 --> 17:33.748
- I did hope the rose
wouldn't do this

17:33.835 --> 17:35.706
before the
photographer arrived,

17:35.793 --> 17:38.840
but, hey, in my job, you learn
you can't control nature.

17:38.927 --> 17:41.538
- Hope it wouldn't
do what, exactly?

17:41.625 --> 17:43.845
- Every few months,
the three-headed rose

17:43.932 --> 17:47.675
whithers, sheds its petals,
and looks just like this.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.851
- Every few months?
- Yes.

17:49.938 --> 17:52.984
But only so it can
grow bigger, brighter,

17:53.072 --> 17:55.074
and even more beautiful.

17:57.293 --> 17:59.600
Hmm, did I forget
to mention that?

17:59.687 --> 18:02.646
- Um, yeah.

18:02.733 --> 18:03.821
- Whoops.

18:03.908 --> 18:05.084
I definitely should
have told you that.

18:05.171 --> 18:06.824
- So the rose is okay?

18:06.911 --> 18:09.000
- It sure is.
- All right!

18:09.088 --> 18:10.567
- Yay!

18:10.654 --> 18:12.178
- But how long does it take
to grow back?

18:12.265 --> 18:13.744
- A few weeks, I'd say.

18:13.831 --> 18:16.007
- But the photographer
is coming now.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.749
- And you have
no three-headed rose.

18:18.836 --> 18:20.795
- You have a no-headed rose!

18:20.882 --> 18:24.451
- Ah, I guess someone else's
flower will be on the cover.

18:24.538 --> 18:26.148
- But you deserve that cover.

18:26.235 --> 18:27.584
- Thanks, Sunny.

18:27.671 --> 18:29.456
I may not have
a three-headed rose,

18:29.543 --> 18:32.154
but I do have a bunch
of great friends.

18:32.241 --> 18:35.723
- A bunch of friends,
just like a bunch of flowers.

18:35.810 --> 18:37.855
That's it!

18:37.942 --> 18:40.597
We're gonna make sure
you still get that cover photo.

18:40.684 --> 18:43.252
Come on, gang.
Peter, we'll be right back.

18:43.339 --> 18:44.862
- Uh, okay.

18:44.949 --> 18:48.562
♪ ♪

18:48.649 --> 18:51.565
- All this time, we've been
looking for a three-headed rose

18:51.652 --> 18:54.089
and we've got one right here.

18:54.176 --> 18:55.569
- Where?
I don't see it.

18:55.656 --> 18:58.224
- Let me show you.
See?

18:58.311 --> 19:01.575
I'm one, Blair is two,
and Rox makes three.

19:01.662 --> 19:03.490
We can be the
three-headed rose--

19:03.577 --> 19:06.232
or at least our hair can be.

19:06.319 --> 19:08.756
- Good plan.
- I like it.

19:08.843 --> 19:10.540
We'll need some red hair chalk.

19:10.627 --> 19:13.326
- And some red glitter.
- Perfect.

19:13.413 --> 19:16.372
Peter will have
a three-headed rose after all.

19:16.459 --> 19:18.069
Let's get to work.

19:18.157 --> 19:19.593
[upbeat music]

19:19.680 --> 19:21.377
- [laughing]

19:21.464 --> 19:22.770
- [giggles]

19:22.857 --> 19:25.599
Some brushing.

19:25.686 --> 19:29.124
Doodle, can you pass
the hair spray?

19:29.211 --> 19:30.908
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.955
[spray hissing]

19:34.042 --> 19:36.436
Now it's taking shape.

19:36.523 --> 19:37.872
Some hair pins.

19:37.959 --> 19:40.179
♪ ♪

19:40.266 --> 19:41.876
Rox, is the chalk ready?

19:41.963 --> 19:43.791
[device beeps]

19:43.878 --> 19:46.228
- Yep, the perfect
shade of red.

19:46.315 --> 19:49.057
- Great.
You're up next.

19:49.144 --> 19:51.102
A little spray here.

19:51.190 --> 19:54.236
A little spray there.

19:54.323 --> 19:55.933
Add some color.

19:56.020 --> 19:59.807
♪ ♪

19:59.894 --> 20:01.243
My turn.

20:01.330 --> 20:08.424
♪ ♪

20:08.511 --> 20:10.818
Done.
Gather 'round, everyone.

20:10.905 --> 20:12.907
- And don't forget
the glitter, Sunny.

20:12.994 --> 20:14.387
- Thanks, Blair.

20:14.474 --> 20:16.824
And now for the
finishing touch.

20:16.911 --> 20:19.392
all: [laughing]

20:19.479 --> 20:21.568
♪ ♪

20:21.655 --> 20:23.004
- Huh?

20:23.091 --> 20:24.658
[gasps]
What's this?

20:24.745 --> 20:27.313
One, two, three roses?

20:27.400 --> 20:28.966
Wow!
I'm impressed, Sunny.

20:29.053 --> 20:31.969
- Thanks, Peter.
- Hmm, I wonder...

20:32.056 --> 20:34.407
Sunny, do you mind
if I add something?

20:34.494 --> 20:37.453
- What do you have in mind?

20:37.540 --> 20:40.630
- Just a little
floral finishing touch.

20:40.717 --> 20:43.285
A little help, Doodle?

20:43.372 --> 20:45.069
[girls laughing]

20:45.156 --> 20:48.116
- [humming]

20:48.203 --> 20:51.772
♪ ♪

20:51.859 --> 20:54.731
There!
- Oh, cool!

20:54.818 --> 20:57.560
- Now you're the
ultimate three-headed rose!

20:57.647 --> 20:59.258
- [gasps]
I like it!

20:59.345 --> 21:00.911
- I agree!

21:00.998 --> 21:04.480
Ready for your photo for
"Flower Monthly Magazine"?

21:04.567 --> 21:06.439
Because I am loving
this new angle--

21:06.526 --> 21:07.962
hair roses.

21:08.049 --> 21:11.357
This is going to be
the best cover ever.

21:11.444 --> 21:13.489
- I love it!
- Come on, Peter.

21:13.576 --> 21:16.100
You need to be
in the picture, too.

21:16.187 --> 21:17.537
Say "rose," everyone!

21:17.624 --> 21:19.582
all: Rose!
[shutter clicks]

21:19.669 --> 21:21.758
- That's my cover photo.

21:21.845 --> 21:25.153
- Everything turned out
rosy after all...[chuckles]

21:25.240 --> 21:28.112
- And that's one
for the Style Files.

21:28.199 --> 21:29.549
- Smile.
[shutter clicks]

21:29.636 --> 21:32.595
♪ ♪

21:32.682 --> 21:34.336
- Don't move.Smile!

21:34.423 --> 21:35.772
[shutter clicks]
- [laughs]

21:35.859 --> 21:38.862
- Perfect!
[girls giggling]

21:42.388 --> 21:43.737
- Hi, it's me, Sunny,

21:43.824 --> 21:46.914
with another look
inside the Style Files.

21:47.001 --> 21:50.091
Wow!
Three beautiful red roses.

21:50.178 --> 21:52.093
[bright music]

21:52.180 --> 21:55.314
For this hairstyle and more,
check out the Style Files

21:55.401 --> 21:57.577
on the Nick Jr. App.

21:57.664 --> 21:59.666
Keep smiling,
keep styling.

21:59.753 --> 22:01.102
[laughs]

22:01.189 --> 22:03.974
[upbeat music]

22:04.061 --> 22:11.373
♪ ♪
